\alpha
x', y'
0 \le \alpha \le 90
x' = BD = BC + CD = FE \cos(90-\alpha) + CD = (h - y) \cos(90-\alpha) + x \cos \alpha
y' = DK = DG + GK = DG + ML \cos (90 - \alpha) = y \cos \alpha + x \cos (90 - \alpha)
\cos(90 - \alpha) = \sin \alpha
x' = BD = (h - y) \sin \alpha + x \cos \alpha
y' = DK = y \cos \alpha + x \sin \alpha
(x', y') = F(x, y, h, \alpha), 0 \le \alpha \le 90
\beta=\alpha-90,\beta=\alpha-180,\beta=\alpha-270
(x', y') = F(h-y, x, w, \alpha-90), 90 \le \alpha \le 180
(x', y') = F(w-x, h-y, h, \alpha-180), 180 \le \alpha \le 270
(x', y') = F(y, w-x, w, \alpha-270), 270 \le \alpha \le 360
x_{new}=(h-y)\cdot sin(A)+x\cdot cos(A)
y_{new}=x\cdot sin(A)+y\cdot cos(A)
